@node play "The game: Installation/Playing"

                             Installation

  The installation is very simple, just place 'Wilinx' where you
want on your hard drive, floppy disk, Ram Disk, etc. No other files
or Libraries are needed. However, your Workbench must have at least
4 colours.

                             How to play?

  The gameplay is quite simple: click on part of the 'wire' or any
'neutral tile' you want to move. If that tile is located next to
the empty space... and that tile can move, particularly if it is a
part of the wire, that tile, or part of the wire, will move towards
the empty space.

  Any tile, either part of the wire or a neutral tile, can move
horizontally, vertically or diagonally... and each type has its
own characteristics:

-Neutral tile: that kind of tile can move anywhere. If it is
               located at the edge of the game board and the empty
space is located at the opposite edge, and both would be next to
each other if the edges were connected together, the tile will
'wraparound' and go to that position.

-Part of a wire: any tile that is part of the wire remain linked to
                 its neighbouring wire part(s), so they cannot be
separated. Also, the links cannot be 'stretched' by more than one
unit. One more thing to remember is that, contrary to the neutral
tiles, no part of the wire can 'wraparound' from one edge to the
opposing edge of the game board...

  To complete the game, you must place all wire parts at the lower
right position of the board, which is indicated by an 'embossed
pathway'. Do this in the least amount of moves.

  Have fun!


Keyboard shortcuts:

 'N'   - Restarts the game.

 'Esc' - Quits the game.

  '7'    '8'    '9'
 Upper    Up   Upper
 left          right

  '4'           '6'
  Left         Right 

  '1'    '2'    '3'
 Lower   Down  Lower
 left          right


OPTIONS:

  New Game: Restarts the game.

  Colour:   Changes the colour of the wire.

